time complexity: O(n log n + m log m)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution first sorts both the tasks and workers arrays. Then, it iterates through the tasks, attempting to assign each task to the next available worker who meets the strength requirement. If a suitable worker is found, the task count is incremented, and the worker index is advanced. If no suitable worker is available and pills remain, a pill is used to increase the strength of the next available worker. This process continues until all tasks have been processed. The sorting operations dominate the time complexity, resulting in O(n log n + m log m). The space complexity is O(1) as the algorithm uses a constant amount of extra space. The energy implications are low as the algorithm performs a limited number of operations.

